  "response": "I don't have personal experiences or feelings, but I can help you think about how someone might react in a situation like that. Many people might feel disappointed or frustrated if their parents didn't buy them something they wanted, like a new mobile phone. It could lead to feelings of sadness, anger, or even understanding, depending on the reasons behind their parents' decision. Talking it out with friends or finding other ways to save up for the phone could also be constructive responses. What about you\u2014how would you feel in that situation?",
